%% Initial Sync Sequence - First-time device registration & data download

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Admin
    participant App as Android App
    participant Room as Room DB
    participant API as Cloud API
    participant PG as PostgreSQL

    Note over User,App: Phase 1: Standalone Setup (default)
    User->>App: Install & open app
    App->>App: Generate TerminalId (UUID)
    App->>Room: Create Terminal (standalone, syncEnabled=false)
    App->>Room: Create default Tenant & Outlet
    Note over App: App fully operational offline

    Note over User,API: Phase 2: Enable Cloud Sync
    User->>App: Open Settings > Cloud Sync
    User->>App: Input Cloud API URL + Registration Token
    App->>API: GET /api/health (validate connection)
    API-->>App: OK

    App->>API: POST /api/terminals/register<br/>{ terminalId, deviceInfo }
    API->>PG: Validate token, create terminal record
    PG-->>API: Terminal registered
    API-->>App: { tenantId, outletId, terminalConfig }

    Note over App,PG: Phase 3: Initial Data Download
    App->>API: GET /api/sync/pull?since=0 (full download)
    API->>PG: Query all master data for tenant/outlet
    PG-->>API: Products, Categories, Users, Settings, Customers, Price Lists, Active Orders

    API-->>App: { changes: [...], latestVersion: N }
    App->>Room: Bulk insert/update all received data
    App->>Room: Set lastSyncVersion = N
    App->>Room: Update Terminal: syncEnabled=true, lastSyncAt=now

    Note over App: Phase 4: Sync Active
    App->>App: Start SyncWorker (periodic)
    App->>API: GET /api/sync/stream (SSE connection)

    Note over App,API: Upload existing local data (if migrating from standalone)
    App->>Room: Query all local entities with syncStatus=PENDING_UPLOAD
    App->>API: POST /api/sync/push { batch: [local data] }
    API-->>App: Accepted / Conflict per item

    Note over App: Device fully operational in cloud mode
